                "invention-title": [
                    "Bidirectional flow hydrogenophilic carbon dioxide methanation device and method",
                    "一种双向流嗜氢型二氧化碳甲烷化的装置与方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to a bidirectional flow hydrogenophilic carbon dioxide methanation device and method, the device comprises a culture stage and a normal operation stage, and each stage comprises a dry biological methanation mode and a biofilm carrier wet soaking mode. In a dry biological methanation mode of a culture stage, firstly, an up-flow gas inlet mode is adopted for culture, then, a down-flow gas inlet mode is adopted for culture, and in a normal operation stage, mixed gas of hydrogen and carbon dioxide is alternately introduced into a gas-phase reaction zone from two ends of the device in an up-flow and down-flow mode; the biological membrane in a static draining state converts hydrogen and carbon dioxide into methane and water. In a wet soaking mode of the biofilm carrier, the porous biofilm carrier is soaked in a nutrient solution, so that pores and microorganisms attached to the surface of the porous biofilm carrier obtain nutrient elements, and growth and reproduction of the microorganisms are promoted. The biomass and carbon dioxide conversion efficiency can be improved under the condition of low cost, and an effective way is provided for recycling of carbon dioxide."
                },
                {
                    "p": "一种双向流嗜氢型二氧化碳甲烷化的装置与方法，包括培养、正常运行两个阶段，两阶段均包括干式生物甲烷化模式和生物膜载体湿式浸泡模式。在培养阶段的干式生物甲烷化模式下，先采用上流式进气方式培养，再改为下流式进气方式培养，正常运行阶段氢气、二氧化碳的混合气体从装置两端以上、下流式交替通入气相反应区，处于静止沥干状态的生物膜将氢气、二氧化碳转化为甲烷和水。生物膜载体湿式浸泡模式，多孔生物膜载体在营养液中浸泡使其孔隙和附着于其表面中微生物获得营养元素，促进微生物生长繁殖。本发明能在低成本条件下提高生物量和二氧化碳转化效率，为二氧化碳资源化提供一种有效途径。"
                }
            ]
